recipes.name: Spaghetti Bolognese
recipes.instructions:
1. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
2. In a separate pan, heat olive oil and sauté garlic and onion.
3. Add ground beef and cook until browned.
4. Pour in tomato sauce, add salt and pepper, and simmer for 15 minutes.
5. Serve sauce over spaghetti.

recipes.name: Chicken Caesar Salad
recipes.instructions:
1. Grill the chicken breast and slice it.
2. Toss the romaine lettuce with Caesar dressing.
3. Top with croutons and parmesan cheese.
4. Add sliced chicken on top and serve.

recipes.name: Vegetable Stir-Fry
recipes.instructions:
1. Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
2. Heat sesame oil in a pan and sauté garlic and ginger.
3. Add vegetables and stir-fry for 5-7 minutes.
4. Add soy sauce and stir to combine.
5. Serve with rice.

recipes.name: Chocolate Chip Cookies
recipes.instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).
2. Cream together butter, sugar, and brown sugar.
3. Beat in eggs and vanilla extract.
4. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
5. Stir in chocolate chips.
6. Drop spoonfuls of dough onto a baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes.
